<SLUG> BC-BKN-MAVERICKS-NOTES-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TRENT SET FOR DEBUT TONIGHT VS. SPURS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By DWAIN PRICE 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   DALLAS _ A familiar face will be on the Reunion Arena court for
the Dallas Mavericks on Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
   Power forward Gary Trent will play in his first regular-season
game of the season against the San Antonio Spurs. Trent has not
played since tearing his left hamstring during an Oct. 21 preseason
game against Toronto.
</P>
<P>
   Mavericks coach/general manager Don Nelson said: ``He's probably
going to play, but limited minutes.''
</P>
<P>
   Nelson doesn't want to rush Trent because the 6-foot-8,
250-pounder is still rusty.
</P>
<P>
   ``When you have a leg injury, you're not allowed to run or
play,'' Trent said. ``So it's easy to get rusty.
</P>
<P>
   ``I just want to rebound and run, and the other things should
come naturally. I want to let the game come to me.''
</P>
<P>
   Trent averaged 16 points and 7.8 rebounds last season and
finished third behind Orlando guard Darrell Armstrong and
Philadelphia guard Eric Snow in the NBA's Most Improved Player
balloting.
</P>
<P>
   The Mavericks have been using a more full-court style without
Trent, but his style is more suited to half-court strategies.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's just going to have to find his niche,'' guard Michael
Finley said. ``I think he's an intelligent basketball player who
knows it's not going to come overnight.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's not going to come in his first game back and give us 48
minutes, and we know that. We're just going to have to groom him
into playing in game conditions, but I don't think he's going to
affect us negatively.'' FINLEY'S STREAK
</P>
<P>
   An injury forced Chicago guard Hersey Hawkins' ironman streak to
end this past weekend at 527 consecutive games played.
</P>
<P>
   Michael Finley is No. 3 on the active list of consecutive games
played. Finley will play in his 320nd consecutive game Tuesday
against San Antonio.
</P>
<P>
   Former Mavericks forward A.C. Green _ now with the Los Angeles
Lakers _ is the overall leader with 1,050 consecutive games played.
San Antonio's Terry Porter is second with 352 consecutive games
played.
</P>
<P>
   Finley will participate in an on-line chat tomorrow at 2 p.m. on
NBA.com.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
