</P>
<P>
   YANKEE-STADIUM (New York) _ For the last five years, George
Steinbrenner has promised repeatedly that he will soon announce
where he wants the Yankees to play when the lease at Yankee Stadium
runs out in 2002. But as Steinbrenner weighs his options, much of
the rest of New York has come to the conclusion that he is really
down to only two: staying in the Bronx in a renovated Yankee
Stadium or in a new ball park. By Richard Sandomir.
