<P>
   TECHNOLOGY
</P>
<P>
   BELLSOUTH-KPN _ATLANTA _ BellSouth announced a clever deal last
week that will eventually give it a large stake in Dutch company
KPN Telecom _ without spending any money. The arrangement, praised
as savvy by analysts and the business press, was touted excitedly
by BellSouth as a way to boost its stock value. KPN stock has
soared, but investors stateside have yawned at BellSouth. Why? Did
BellSouth oversell this? Where does it leave the company? And where
does it lead? (Kanell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 25.
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT/ARTS
</P>
<P>
   GWTW-MUSEUM _ ATLANTA _ A look at the new memorabilia museum
opening Dec. 15 at the Gone With the Wind museum. It's being billed
as a new building of exhibits and artifacts focusing on the movie's
phenomenon. It includes the front door (!) of Tara from the movie
set. This opening turns the Mitchell House &AMP; Museum into a
two-block historic site. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   JANE-POWELL _ Jane Powell, the ingenue songbird of the golden
era of the M-G-M MGM movie musicals, doesn't mind talking about the
past, but she would much rather look ahead. After all, at 70, the
still perky Powell has a new movie waiting to be released and a
couple of television projects to be aired. ``Just a few things to
keep me off the streets,'' she says. And she is taking computer
lessons to get ready for the next millennium. (Erstein, Palm Beach
Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   ISAAC-STERN WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Isaac Stern is looking
forward to musical life after 79. We chat with the legendary
violinist and author. (Passy, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   LIFESTYLE
</P>
<P>
   PROSTATE-SCREENING _ DAYTON, Ohio _ Thor Industries has begun a
national tour in a custom-built recreational vehicle to deliver
free prostate cancer screenings to 10,000 men older than 40 in
upcoming months. The tour is targeting RV owners at RV shows and
other public forums, since a majority of RV owners are over 40.
Thor is the second-largest manufacturer of RVs and largest midsized
bus manufacturer in North America. (Lamb, Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   CYSTIC-FIBROSIS _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Every night, Bill and
Jerri Chesney tap their children's chests, over and over again, to
keep them from drowning. Courtney, 8, and Taylor, 5, have cystic
fibrosis, a disease that tricks the body into producing excess
mucus, which coats the pancreas and the lungs, inhibiting digestion
and breathing. The phlegmy superflux must be expelled daily, or the
children will be left gasping for air, like fish on dry land. Life
is a struggle for the Chesney family, but their faith is strong.
(Browning, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   HOME AND GARDEN
</P>
<P>
   GARDENING-LIFE _ A gardening column by Lee May. Sally Ann Giray
has lost control, and her life's all the better for it. A poet,
storyteller, playwright, actress and gardener, Giray gave in to the
pulls of words and flowers and spirituality, combining the three to
produce a book of poems, ``Prayers from the Flowers.'' Lee May
discovers her sources of inspiration. (May, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   Eds: Embargoed for Thursday, Dec. 16
</P>
<P>
   NUTSNBOLTS _ The use of gas fireplaces and gas logs has
increased so dramatically in recent years that sales of gas
fireplaces now easily outstrip sales of wood-burning fireplaces,
stoves, fireplace inserts and pellet stoves. According to the
Hearth Product Association, sales of gas logs and fireplaces grew
from 149,000 units in in 1992 to nearly 800,000 in 1998. Sales of
wood-burning appliances were at 541,000 in 1998. It's not
surprising, then, that problems associated with gas-burning
fireplaces are increasing, too. (Cummings, Dayton Daily News). 27.
MOVED SATURDAY
</P>
<P>
   PARTY-STEMWARE _ Professional party planners will tell you their
most fun and exciting affairs result from breaking the rules. It's
even fun to let guests help plan the occasion. And with the array
of designs in stemware these days _ from whimsical
conversation-starters to elegant art glass _ the choices are
endless. Our stemware primer helps take the mystery out of what to
use when and how. (Flanders, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). WITH
PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   Eds: Embargoed for Thursday, Dec. 16
</P>
<P>
   HOLIDAY-TABLE _ ``Keep the food and drink simple but the
presentation grand.'' Those are words to live by for those planning
to entertain over the next few weeks. Two experts share quick table
top decorating tips for those grand occasions. (Flanders, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   Eds: Embargoed for Thursday, Dec. 16
</P>
<P>
   SECURITY-HOLIDAY _The holiday season is supposed to be a time of
good cheer, but it's also a time when home burglaries are at their
highest, according to law enforcement experts. Burglary is a crime
of opportunity where the objective is to get in and out of a home
as quickly as possible. But by following a few basic guidelines you
can discourage unwanted intruders from ever attempting to get in.
(AHill, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). WITH ILLUSTRATION.
</P>
