<P>
   KLEINBERG-COLUMN _ It used to be that to have a memento from a
famous or infamous person was to have something rare; a
conversation piece. In this last decade of the 1900s, however, it
is rare that someone isn't collecting mementos. Late last month,
for example, more than 350 people turned out in San Diego to bid
for the possessions of the Heaven's Gate cult whose 39 in-house
fanatics did away with themselves in a mass suicide. (Kleinberg,
Cox News Service.) MOVED MONDAY.
</P>
<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ Have you heard about the Northwest pilot who
held up a flight for an hour because he didn't like the meal he was
served? Walked off the airplane, past the airport jiffy-junk food
establishments, got into a cab and went to get himself some real
food. The airline had a little surprise for him when he got back.
They fired him. In the case of this 22-year veteran of airline
abuse, I would have thrown my discomfort to the winds and cheered
the hero who risked it all to protest his company's practice of
serving food that, unless you've seen a third-world dumpster for
yourself, cannot be aptly described. (Schuett, Cox News Service)
MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   YOUNG-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ Listen to the children _ lean, mean
and obscene. They know not what they do, what consequences words
can carry. We must again teach them to look before they bleep, and
remind ourselves as well. That's what Chick Lewis' mission has
been. (Young, Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   WIGGINS-COLUMN _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Tennis court lines are
not supposed to be wavy, so my wife's first reaction was, ``That's
odd.'' During a pause in a clinic she was teaching, she
experimented, closing each eye in turn. Slight problem in the left
eye. Time for an appointment. After dilation and an hour of charts
and lights, the doctor offered this somber finding: Cataracts in
both eyes, beginning of glaucoma in both eyes, and a ``wet''
retina, indicative of bleeding. Stunned, Nellie asked: ``What can I
do?'' This is the story of what Nellie, her HMO and her doctors
did. (Wiggins, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
