<P>
   GWTW-MUSEUM _ ATLANTA _ A look at the new memorabilia museum
opening Dec. 15 at the Gone With the Wind museum. It's being billed
as a new building of exhibits and artifacts focusing on the movie's
phenomenon. It includes the front door (!) of Tara from the movie
set. This opening turns the Mitchell House &AMP; Museum into a
two-block historic site. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   JANE-POWELL _ Jane Powell, the ingenue songbird of the golden
era of the M-G-M MGM movie musicals, doesn't mind talking about the
past, but she would much rather look ahead. After all, at 70, the
still perky Powell has a new movie waiting to be released and a
couple of television projects to be aired. ``Just a few things to
keep me off the streets,'' she says. And she is taking computer
lessons to get ready for the next millennium. (Erstein, Palm Beach
Post) MOVED.
