   HOME AND GARDEN
</P>
<P>
   GARDENING-LIFE _ A gardening column by Lee May. Sally Ann Giray
has lost control, and her life's all the better for it. A poet,
storyteller, playwright, actress and gardener, Giray gave in to the
pulls of words and flowers and spirituality, combining the three to
produce a book of poems, ``Prayers from the Flowers.'' Lee May
discovers her sources of inspiration. (May, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
