   Eds: Embargoed for Thursday, Dec. 16
</P>
<P>
   NUTSNBOLTS _ The use of gas fireplaces and gas logs has
increased so dramatically in recent years that sales of gas
fireplaces now easily outstrip sales of wood-burning fireplaces,
stoves, fireplace inserts and pellet stoves. According to the
Hearth Product Association, sales of gas logs and fireplaces grew
from 149,000 units in in 1992 to nearly 800,000 in 1998. Sales of
wood-burning appliances were at 541,000 in 1998. It's not
surprising, then, that problems associated with gas-burning
fireplaces are increasing, too. (Cummings, Dayton Daily News). 27.
MOVED SATURDAY
</P>
<P>
   PARTY-STEMWARE _ Professional party planners will tell you their
most fun and exciting affairs result from breaking the rules. It's
even fun to let guests help plan the occasion. And with the array
of designs in stemware these days _ from whimsical
conversation-starters to elegant art glass _ the choices are
endless. Our stemware primer helps take the mystery out of what to
use when and how. (Flanders, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). WITH
PHOTOS.
</P>
