</P>
<P>
   Nevertheless that court, one of the most vigorously conservative
in the country, took up the issue at the prompting of Paul Cassell,
a law professor at the University of Utah, who has waged a lonely
campaign against the Miranda decision in law journals and court
briefs.
</P>
<P>
   The Supreme Court, almost as unusually, has asked Cassell to
