annual man-of-the-year cover, is searching for a public consensus
on a person of the century. The results will be in the Dec. 27
magazine. The pundits' favorite seems to be Franklin D. Roosevelt,
but a Time online poll leans toward Elvis Presley (honest).This is
an interesting exercise, but a case can be made for choosing many
people, not just one. By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
