shisk-kebab cicadas, black ants on hard-boiled eggs and live
scorpions crawling up a 10-inch pagoda. It's a dining craze in
China, endorsed by doctors of traditional Chinese medicine,
health-food enthusiasts and the nation's new rich. By Indira A.R.
Lakshmanan. 1300 words.
