A8825 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r l BC-TRIVIA-Q&AMP;A-TEX     12-14 0335
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TRIVIA-Q&AMP;A-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
HOW TO FINALLY CLAIM SOME UNCLAIMED MONEY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: I was contacted a few years ago about some unclaimed money
coming to me in California, but I was not told how much or where it
was from. Who can I contact about collecting this?
</P>
<P>
   _ A.O., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: The California state controller's office handles unclaimed
funds like the one you were contacted about. Your name shows up in
the database under a Cudahy, Calif., address for a Golden State
Bank savings or credit union account that contained $35.91.
</P>
<P>
   For information on how to document a claim and collect funds in
California, call (916) 323-2827 or visit the Web site
www.sco.ca.gov/col/ucp. The site also can be used to search the
entire database for any name.
</P>
<P>
   In Texas, to search for unclaimed funds, call (800) 654-3463 or
visit the Web site
www.window.state.tx.us/comptrol/unclprop/upsearch.html.
</P>
<P>
   States do not charge for sending out unclaimed funds and many
now offer searchable databases on the Web. To find these, visit the
site www.unclaimed.org.
</P>
<P>
   Q: In the '60s, there was a popular light called the Rain Lamp
that pumped oil up and down a series of nylon strings. Where can I
find oil for one of these?
</P>
<P>
   _ H.L., Granbury, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: Hippie Heaven in Piedmont, S.C., sells both Rain Lamps and
replacement oil. Oil costs $5.75 per pint with a three-pint
minimum, and there is a $3 shipping charge, making the total
$20.25.
</P>
<P>
   To order, call (864) 845-7032 or visit the Web site
www.hippieheaven.net. Hippie Heaven also sells black lights, wave
machines, art deco lamps, disco lights, and other '60s- and
'70s-inspired products.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-12-14-99 1833EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
