The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Wednesday, Dec. 15. If you
have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
MONUMENTS (Phoenix) - Arizona Gov. Jane Hull and Republican members
of Arizona's congressional delegation are blasting Interior
Secretary Brucer Babbitt's proposals to create two new monuments in
Arizona. But their objections may be too late. President Clinton
indicated Tuesday that he is leaning toward signing an executive
order soon that would protect areas northwest of the Grand Canyon
and north of Phoenix from uranium mining and urban sprawl. By STEVE
YOZWIAK. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
