<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CCE-CHANGES-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    CCE continues shake-up
 &HT;    By Henry Unger
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Coca-Cola Enterprises announced more management
changes Tuesday as President and Chief Executive Officer Henry
Schimberg prepares to step down in two weeks.
</P>
<P>
   The Coke system's largest bottler named four new senior vice
presidents, including a new special assistant to the CEO.
</P>
<P>
   ``These appointments not only reflect the talents of each
individual, but they also demonstrate the depth of the management
team at Coca-Cola Enterprises,'' Chairman Summerfield K. Johnston
Jr. said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
   Management depth is an important issue as CCE goes forward
because losing Schimberg, one of the most respected executives in
the beverage industry, has been a concern on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
   The changes reflect the bottler's effort to restructure
management in the wake of Schimberg's October decision to retire
four months earlier than expected.
</P>
<P>
   On Jan. 1, Johnston, 66, will take over Schimberg's CEO duties
on an interim basis until the company names a permanent
replacement. Chief Operating Officer John Alm will take over as
president Jan. 1. Many analysts expect Alm, 53, to eventually be
named CEO.
</P>
<P>
   The following promotions were announced Tuesday after the board
meeting at the company's headquarters:
</P>
<P>
   _ Vicki R. Palmer, currently vice president and treasurer, was
named senior vice president, treasurer and special assistant to the
CEO. In the newly created position as special assistant, Palmer
will oversee corporate affairs and help with organizational
development efforts. She will continue managing CCE's $11 billion
debt portfolio, $3 billion pension plan and 401(k) investments.
</P>
<P>
   _ Patrick J. Mannelly, who was named chief financial officer in
April, was named senior vice president and chief financial officer.
He is a former corporate vice president for finance and
administration and chief financial officer for CCE's Western North
America Group.
</P>
<P>
   _ John R. Parker Jr., who was named general counsel in July, was
named senior vice president and general counsel.
</P>
<P>
   _ John H. Downs Jr. was named senior vice president of public
affairs. He has been vice president of public affairs since 1989.
</P>
<P>
   CCE's stock closed at $61.43 3/4 Tuesday, down 6 1/4 cents.
</P>
<P>
   Henry Unger writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution,
Atlanta, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
