<SLUG> BC-FBC-BLACK-BOWLS-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Richardson lobs 1st salvo at `third-rated' Hampton
 &HT;    By Earnest Reese
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Southern University coach Pete Richardson fired the
first shot heading into the McDonald's Heritage Bowl on Saturday at
the Georgia Dome.
</P>
<P>
   Richardson, whose team finished 11-1 and will represent the
Southwestern Athletic Conference in the event for the fifth
consecutive year, referred to opponent Hampton University as ``a
third-rated team.'' Hampton (7-4) finished third in the Mid-Eastern
Athletic Conference behind North Carolina A&AMP;T and Florida A&AMP;M, but
was chosen to compete in the Heritage Bowl after the other two
teams advanced to the Division I-AA playoffs.
</P>
<P>
   The remark upset Hampton coach Joe Taylor, who got the copier
machines busy.
</P>
<P>
   ``We had the comment run off, and it's up on the walls in our
locker room,'' Taylor said. ``No question about it. We're really
looking forward to this game.''
</P>
<P>
   Southern defeated Hampton 26-6 during the regular season. Its
lone loss _ a 65-18 shellacking _ came against Florida A&AMP;M, the
second-place team from the MEAC.
</P>
<P>
   Well-rested
</P>
<P>
   Hampton hasn't played since Nov. 20 against Morgan State and
will be well-rested entering the game. Southern, on the other hand,
faced Grambling on Nov. 27 in the Bayou Classic in New Orleans and
Jackson State last weekend in the first SWAC championship game in
Birmingham.
</P>
<P>
   ``Ordinarily, you would say that if you've recently played, it's
an advantage,'' Taylor said. ``But the fact that we're healthy
should really help us.''
</P>
<P>
   Gift bags
</P>
<P>
   Sports &AMP; Entertainment Direct has prepared 50,000 bags of
assorted gifts to be handed out at the Heritage Bowl. If that many
people attend the game, bowl executive director Craig Cason would
be ecstatic.
</P>
<P>
   Pioneer Bowl
</P>
<P>
   The third Pioneer Bowl, which will match SIAC representative
Tuskegee against CIAA champion Winston-Salem State, will follow the
Heritage Bowl in the Georgia Dome at 6 p.m. Saturday. Tickets to
the Pioneer Bowl are $15 and separate from the Heritage Bowl.
</P>
<P>
   Earnest Reese writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution,
Atlanta, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
