   (NYT26) WASHINGTON -- Dec. 14, 1999 -- Y2K-COX -- The White
House Y2K czar, John Koskinen, told the National Press Club that
because major industries ``are basically done with their Y2K work
... we do not expect to see major national failures'' in key
sectors, such as power generation, telecommunications or
transportation. He went on though, to urge Americans to prepare for
a few days of potential disruptions in business routines. (Rick
McKay/The New York Times)
