U.S. Senator Bill Bradley talks about campaign finance reform on
Tuesday. Nearly losing re-election to the Senate in 1990 against
now Gov. Christine Whitman of New Jersey shook his confidence in
himself and his staff, triggering an intense bout of introspection
that helped change the course of his career, Bradley and his
friends say. (Jack Manning/The New York Times)
</P>
