MIDEAST-HEIGHTS-2 -- Israelis enjoy the hot springs of Hamat Gader
in the Golan Heights. The resumption of talks with Syria on an
Israeli withdrawal from the strategic Golan in exchange for peace,
which are to begin in Washington on Wednesday, has confronted the
settlers with a real prospect of losing homes, orchards and
businesses in which they have invested decades of their lives.
Hamat Gader is part of the region which could be returned to Syria
in a deal. (Rina Castelnuovo/The New York Times)
</P>
